{
  "id": "RAW_7d258a0d",
  "title": "NVIDIA BioNeMo 智能体工具包将生物分子模型转化为药物发现 AI 智能体的可调用技能",
  "url": "https://www.marktechpost.com/2026/06/29/nvidia-bionemo-agent-toolkit-turns-biomolecular-models-into-callable-skills-for-ai-agents-in-drug-discovery/",
  "date": "2026-06-30 03:06:50",
  "author": "Asif Razzaq",
  "siteName": "MarkTechPost",
  "content": "<html>\n <head></head>\n <body>\n  <p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">AI scientists are becoming a new interface for scientific computing. These agents read papers, write code, generate hypotheses, call APIs, and inspect files. But science is not software engineering. No test suite turns green when a hypothesis is correct. Discovery stays iterative, uncertain, and grounded in the physical world.</p>\n  <p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">That gap is what NVIDIA is targeting. NVIDIA published a hands-on walkthrough for its <a href=\"https://github.com/NVIDIA-BioNeMo/bionemo-agent-toolkit\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">BioNeMo Agent Toolkit</a>. The argument is direct. A general coding agent pointed at biology will not produce new medicines. In biomolecular research, an agent’s ceiling is set by the tools it can use reliably, correctly, and efficiently.</p>\n  <h3 id=\"h-tl-dr\" class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>TL;DR</strong></h3>\n  <ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n   <li>BioNeMo Agent Toolkit packages NVIDIA biomolecular models as documented, callable agent skills.</li>\n   <li>Skills span protein folding, docking, generative chemistry, genomics, and protein design.</li>\n   <li>NVIDIA reports task completion rising from 57.1% to 100% with skills.</li>\n   <li>Agents averaged 2x more passing assertions per 1,000 tokens.</li>\n   <li>Hosted NIM endpoints suit quick access; local NIM suits repeated iteration.</li>\n  </ul>\n  <h2 id=\"h-interactive-explainer\" class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>Interactive Explainer</strong></h2>\n  <!-- BioNeMo AI Scientist Demo by Marktechpost — paste into a WordPress \"Custom HTML\" block -->\n  <iframe class=\"lazyload\" id=\"bionemo-demo\" title=\"BioNeMo AI Scientist Workflow Simulator\" scrolling=\"no\" srcdoc=\"&lt;!DOCTYPE html&gt;\n&lt;html lang=&quot;en&quot;&gt;\n&lt;head&gt;\n&lt;meta charset=&quot;UTF-8&quot;&gt;\n&lt;meta name=&quot;viewport&quot; content=&quot;width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0&quot;&gt;\n&lt;title&gt;BioNeMo AI Scientist — Workflow Simulator&lt;/title&gt;\n&lt;style&gt;\n  :root{\n    --bg:#F6F8F2;\n    --surface:#FFFFFF;\n    --surface-2:#F1F5EA;\n    --ink:#16240E;\n    --ink-soft:#54614A;\n    --line:#E2E8D6;\n    --green:#76B900;\n    --green-deep:#5C9100;\n    --teal:#0B7E84;\n    --amber:#C77B12;\n    --red:#C0392B;\n    --radius:14px;\n    --mono:&quot;JetBrains Mono&quot;,ui-monospace,&quot;SF Mono&quot;,Menlo,Consolas,monospace;\n    --sans:&quot;Inter&quot;,system-ui,-apple-system,Segoe UI,Roboto,Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif;\n  }\n  *{box-sizing:border-box}\n  body{margin:0;background:var(--bg);font-family:var(--sans);color:var(--ink);\n    -webkit-font-smoothing:antialiased;line-height:1.5}\n  .bn-wrap{max-width:880px;margin:0 auto;padding:22px}\n\n  /* header */\n  .bn-head{display:flex;align-items:flex-start;gap:14px;margin-bottom:18px}\n  .bn-mark{flex:0 0 auto;width:44px;height:44px;border-radius:11px;\n    background:linear-gradient(135deg,var(--green),var(--green-deep));\n    display:grid;place-items:center;box-shadow:0 4px 14px rgba(118,185,0,.28)}\n  .bn-mark svg{width:26px;height:26px}\n  .bn-eyebrow{font-family:var(--mono);font-size:11px;letter-spacing:.14em;\n    text-transform:uppercase;color:var(--green-deep);font-weight:600;margin:0 0 3px}\n  .bn-title{font-size:21px;font-weight:700;margin:0;letter-spacing:-.01em}\n  .bn-sub{margin:4px 0 0;color:var(--ink-soft);font-size:13.5px;max-width:62ch}\n\n  /* panel */\n  .bn-panel{background:var(--surface);border:1px solid var(--line);\n    border-radius:var(--radius);padding:18px;margin-bottom:16px;\n    box-shadow:0 1px 2px rgba(22,36,14,.04)}\n  .bn-label{font-family:var(--mono);font-size:11px;letter-spacing:.1em;\n    text-transform:uppercase;color:var(--ink-soft);font-weight:600;margin:0 0 11px}\n\n  /* task cards */\n  .bn-tasks{display:grid;grid-template-columns:repeat(4,1fr);gap:10px}\n  .bn-task{appearance:none;text-align:left;cursor:pointer;background:var(--surface-2);\n    border:1.5px solid var(--line);border-radius:11px;padding:12px 12px 13px;\n    transition:border-color .15s,background .15s,transform .08s;font-family:inherit}\n  .bn-task:hover{border-color:#C5D4AF}\n  .bn-task:active{transform:translateY(1px)}\n  .bn-task.is-on{border-color:var(--green);background:#fff;\n    box-shadow:0 0 0 3px rgba(118,185,0,.14)}\n  .bn-task-ico{font-size:18px;line-height:1}\n  .bn-task-name{display:block;font-weight:650;font-size:13.5px;margin:8px 0 2px}\n  .bn-task-skill{display:block;font-family:var(--mono);font-size:10.5px;color:var(--teal)}\n\n  /* controls row */\n  .bn-ctrls{display:flex;align-items:center;flex-wrap:wrap;gap:14px;margin-top:16px}\n  .bn-toggle{display:inline-flex;align-items:center;gap:9px;cursor:pointer;user-select:none}\n  .bn-switch{width:42px;height:24px;border-radius:99px;background:#CBD5BD;position:relative;\n    transition:background .18s;flex:0 0 auto}\n  .bn-switch::after{content:&quot;&quot;;position:absolute;top:3px;left:3px;width:18px;height:18px;\n    border-radius:50%;background:#fff;transition:transform .18s;box-shadow:0 1px 3px rgba(0,0,0,.2)}\n  .bn-toggle.is-on .bn-switch{background:var(--green)}\n  .bn-toggle.is-on .bn-switch::after{transform:translateX(18px)}\n  .bn-toggle-txt{font-size:13px;font-weight:600}\n  .bn-toggle-txt small{display:block;font-weight:400;color:var(--ink-soft);font-size:11.5px}\n  .bn-run{margin-left:auto;appearance:none;border:0;cursor:pointer;font-family:inherit;\n    font-weight:650;font-size:14px;color:#10210A;background:var(--green);\n    padding:11px 22px;border-radius:10px;transition:background .15s,opacity .15s}\n  .bn-run:hover{background:var(--green-deep);color:#fff}\n  .bn-run:disabled{opacity:.55;cursor:default}\n\n  /* loop */\n  .bn-grid{display:grid;grid-template-columns:1.25fr 1fr;gap:16px}\n  @media(max-width:680px){.bn-grid{grid-template-columns:1fr}.bn-tasks{grid-template-columns:repeat(2,1fr)}}\n  .bn-steps{list-style:none;margin:0;padding:0}\n  .bn-step{display:flex;gap:11px;align-items:flex-start;padding:10px 0;\n    border-bottom:1px dashed var(--line);opacity:.45;transition:opacity .25s}\n  .bn-step:last-child{border-bottom:0}\n  .bn-step.is-live{opacity:1}\n  .bn-step.is-done{opacity:1}\n  .bn-dot{flex:0 0 auto;width:22px;height:22px;border-radius:50%;border:2px solid var(--line);\n    display:grid;place-items:center;font-size:12px;font-weight:700;color:var(--ink-soft);\n    background:#fff;transition:all .25s}\n  .bn-step.is-live .bn-dot{border-color:var(--green);color:var(--green-deep);\n    animation:bn-pulse 1s infinite}\n  .bn-step.is-done .bn-dot{border-color:var(--green);background:var(--green);color:#fff}\n  .bn-step.is-fail .bn-dot{border-color:var(--red);background:var(--red);color:#fff}\n  @keyframes bn-pulse{0%,100%{box-shadow:0 0 0 0 rgba(118,185,0,.35)}50%{box-shadow:0 0 0 5px rgba(118,185,0,0)}}\n  .bn-step-name{font-weight:600;font-size:13.5px;margin:1px 0 1px}\n  .bn-step-note{font-size:12px;color:var(--ink-soft);font-family:var(--mono)}\n  .bn-step.is-fail .bn-step-note{color:var(--red)}\n\n  /* artifact card */\n  .bn-art{background:var(--surface-2);border:1px solid var(--line);border-radius:11px;\n    padding:14px;height:100%}\n  .bn-art-row{display:flex;justify-content:space-between;gap:8px;padding:7px 0;\n    border-bottom:1px solid var(--line);font-size:12.5px}\n  .bn-art-row:last-child{border-bottom:0}\n  .bn-art-k{color:var(--ink-soft)}\n  .bn-art-v{font-family:var(--mono);text-align:right;font-weight:600}\n  .bn-chip{display:inline-block;font-family:var(--mono);font-size:11px;font-weight:600;\n    padding:2px 8px;border-radius:6px;background:rgba(11,126,132,.1);color:var(--teal)}\n  .bn-status{margin-top:12px;font-size:12.5px;font-family:var(--mono);font-weight:600;\n    padding:9px 11px;border-radius:8px;display:flex;gap:7px;align-items:center}\n  .bn-status.ok{background:rgba(118,185,0,.12);color:var(--green-deep)}\n  .bn-status.warn{background:rgba(199,123,18,.12);color:var(--amber)}\n  .bn-status.idle{background:var(--surface-2);color:var(--ink-soft)}\n\n  /* metrics */\n  .bn-metrics{display:grid;grid-template-columns:1fr 1fr;gap:16px}\n  @media(max-width:680px){.bn-metrics{grid-template-columns:1fr}}\n  .bn-metric-name{font-size:12.5px;font-weight:600;margin:0 0 8px;display:flex;\n    justify-content:space-between}\n  .bn-metric-name b{font-family:var(--mono);color:var(--green-deep)}\n  .bn-bar{height:12px;border-radius:99px;background:var(--surface-2);overflow:hidden;\n    border:1px solid var(--line)}\n  .bn-bar-fill{display:block;height:100%;width:0;border-radius:99px;\n    background:linear-gradient(90deg,var(--green),var(--green-deep));\n    transition:width .9s cubic-bezier(.4,0,.2,1)}\n  .bn-metric-foot{font-size:11px;color:var(--ink-soft);margin:7px 0 0}\n\n  /* footer */\n  .bn-foot{display:flex;justify-content:space-between;align-items:center;gap:10px;\n    flex-wrap:wrap;margin-top:4px;padding-top:14px;border-top:1px solid var(--line)}\n  .bn-foot-note{font-size:11px;color:var(--ink-soft);max-width:48ch}\n  .bn-brand{font-family:var(--mono);font-size:11.5px;font-weight:600}\n  .bn-brand b{color:var(--green-deep)}\n&lt;/style&gt;\n&lt;/head&gt;\n&lt;body&gt;\n&lt;div class=&quot;bn-wrap&quot; id=&quot;bnRoot&quot;&gt;\n\n  &lt;div class=&quot;bn-head&quot;&gt;\n    &lt;div class=&quot;bn-mark&quot; aria-hidden=&quot;true&quot;&gt;\n      &lt;svg viewBox=&quot;0 0 24 24&quot; fill=&quot;none&quot; stroke=&quot;#fff&quot; stroke-width=&quot;2&quot; stroke-linecap=&quot;round&quot;&gt;\n        &lt;path d=&quot;M6 3c4 3 8 3 12 0M6 21c4-3 8-3 12 0M6 3c0 6 0 12 0 18M18 3c0 6 0 12 0 18&quot;/&gt;\n        &lt;path d=&quot;M7 8h10M7 16h10&quot; stroke-width=&quot;1.5&quot;/&gt;\n      &lt;/svg&gt;\n    &lt;/div&gt;\n    &lt;div&gt;\n      &lt;p class=&quot;bn-eyebrow&quot;&gt;BioNeMo Agent Toolkit · Interactive&lt;/p&gt;\n      &lt;h2 class=&quot;bn-title&quot;&gt;AI Scientist Workflow Simulator&lt;/h2&gt;\n      &lt;p class=&quot;bn-sub&quot;&gt;Pick a scientific goal, then watch the agent loop run a BioNeMo Skill. Toggle skills on or off to see how completion and token efficiency change.&lt;/p&gt;\n    &lt;/div&gt;\n  &lt;/div&gt;\n\n  &lt;!-- task + controls --&gt;\n  &lt;div class=&quot;bn-panel&quot;&gt;\n    &lt;p class=&quot;bn-label&quot;&gt;1 · Choose a scientific goal&lt;/p&gt;\n    &lt;div class=&quot;bn-tasks&quot; id=&quot;bnTasks&quot;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;\n\n    &lt;div class=&quot;bn-ctrls&quot;&gt;\n      &lt;div class=&quot;bn-toggle is-on&quot; id=&quot;bnSkillToggle&quot; role=&quot;switch&quot; aria-checked=&quot;true&quot; tabindex=&quot;0&quot;&gt;\n        &lt;span class=&quot;bn-switch&quot;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;\n        &lt;span class=&quot;bn-toggle-txt&quot;&gt;BioNeMo Skills\n          &lt;small id=&quot;bnToggleSub&quot;&gt;On — agent reads the skill&lt;/small&gt;\n        &lt;/span&gt;\n      &lt;/div&gt;\n      &lt;button class=&quot;bn-run&quot; id=&quot;bnRun&quot;&gt;Run agent loop&lt;/button&gt;\n    &lt;/div&gt;\n  &lt;/div&gt;\n\n  &lt;!-- loop + artifact --&gt;\n  &lt;div class=&quot;bn-panel&quot;&gt;\n    &lt;p class=&quot;bn-label&quot;&gt;2 · Agent loop&lt;/p&gt;\n    &lt;div class=&quot;bn-grid&quot;&gt;\n      &lt;ul class=&quot;bn-steps&quot; id=&quot;bnSteps&quot;&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;\n      &lt;div class=&quot;bn-art&quot; id=&quot;bnArt&quot;&gt;\n        &lt;div class=&quot;bn-art-row&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;bn-art-k&quot;&gt;Capability&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;bn-art-v&quot; id=&quot;bnCap&quot;&gt;—&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;\n        &lt;div class=&quot;bn-art-row&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;bn-art-k&quot;&gt;Model / Skill&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;bn-art-v&quot; id=&quot;bnModel&quot;&gt;—&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;\n        &lt;div class=&quot;bn-art-row&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;bn-art-k&quot;&gt;Input&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;bn-art-v&quot; id=&quot;bnInput&quot;&gt;—&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;\n        &lt;div class=&quot;bn-art-row&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;bn-art-k&quot;&gt;Expected artifact&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;bn-art-v&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;bn-chip&quot; id=&quot;bnArtType&quot;&gt;—&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;\n        &lt;div class=&quot;bn-status idle&quot; id=&quot;bnStatus&quot;&gt;Idle — select a goal and run.&lt;/div&gt;\n      &lt;/div&gt;\n    &lt;/div&gt;\n  &lt;/div&gt;\n\n  &lt;!-- metrics --&gt;\n  &lt;div class=&quot;bn-panel&quot;&gt;\n    &lt;p class=&quot;bn-label&quot;&gt;3 · Reported impact &lt;span style=&quot;font-weight:400;text-transform:none;letter-spacing:0&quot;&gt;(NVIDIA averages, Codex CLI + GPT-5.5 fast)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\n    &lt;div class=&quot;bn-metrics&quot;&gt;\n      &lt;div&gt;\n        &lt;p class=&quot;bn-metric-name&quot;&gt;Task completion &lt;b id=&quot;bnComplVal&quot;&gt;100%&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\n        &lt;div class=&quot;bn-bar&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;bn-bar-fill&quot; id=&quot;bnComplBar&quot;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;\n        &lt;p class=&quot;bn-metric-foot&quot;&gt;Without skills: 57.1% · With skills: 100%&lt;/p&gt;\n      &lt;/div&gt;\n      &lt;div&gt;\n        &lt;p class=&quot;bn-metric-name&quot;&gt;Passing assertions / 1k tokens &lt;b id=&quot;bnEffVal&quot;&gt;2.0×&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\n        &lt;div class=&quot;bn-bar&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;bn-bar-fill&quot; id=&quot;bnEffBar&quot;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;\n        &lt;p class=&quot;bn-metric-foot&quot;&gt;With skills: ~2× more passing assertions per 1k tokens&lt;/p&gt;\n      &lt;/div&gt;\n    &lt;/div&gt;\n\n    &lt;div class=&quot;bn-foot&quot;&gt;\n      &lt;p class=&quot;bn-foot-note&quot;&gt;Illustrative simulation for explanation only. Not connected to live NVIDIA NIM endpoints. Figures reflect results NVIDIA reported on June 23, 2026.&lt;/p&gt;\n      &lt;p class=&quot;bn-brand&quot;&gt;Built by &lt;b&gt;Marktechpost&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\n    &lt;/div&gt;\n  &lt;/div&gt;\n\n&lt;/div&gt;\n\n&lt;script&gt;\n(function(){\n  var TASKS = {\n    fold: {icon:&quot;\\uD83E\\uDDEC&quot;, name:&quot;Fold a peptide&quot;, skill:&quot;OpenFold3&quot;,\n      cap:&quot;Structure prediction&quot;, model:&quot;OpenFold3 (NIM)&quot;,\n      input:&quot;MKTVRQERLKSIVR&quot;, artifact:&quot;CIF&quot;,\n      prepNote:&quot;sequence validated · MSA optional&quot;,\n      failStep:1, failNote:&quot;can't pick input format&quot;},\n    dock: {icon:&quot;\\uD83E\\uDDF2&quot;, name:&quot;Dock a ligand&quot;, skill:&quot;DiffDock&quot;,\n      cap:&quot;Molecular docking&quot;, model:&quot;DiffDock (NIM)&quot;,\n      input:&quot;protein + ligand&quot;, artifact:&quot;SDF pose&quot;,\n      prepNote:&quot;receptor + ligand parsed&quot;,\n      failStep:2, failNote:&quot;endpoint + params unknown&quot;},\n    gen: {icon:&quot;\\u269B\\uFE0F&quot;, name:&quot;Generate molecules&quot;, skill:&quot;GenMol&quot;,\n      cap:&quot;Generative chemistry&quot;, model:&quot;GenMol (NIM)&quot;,\n      input:&quot;seed fragment&quot;, artifact:&quot;SDF / SMILES&quot;,\n      prepNote:&quot;fragment encoded&quot;,\n      failStep:0, failNote:&quot;wrong model selected&quot;},\n    binder: {icon:&quot;\\uD83D\\uDD17&quot;, name:&quot;Design a binder&quot;, skill:&quot;binder workflow&quot;,\n      cap:&quot;Protein binder design&quot;, model:&quot;RFdiffusion \\u2192 ProteinMPNN \\u2192 OpenFold3&quot;,\n      input:&quot;target protein&quot;, artifact:&quot;sequence + fold&quot;,\n      prepNote:&quot;3-step workflow chained&quot;,\n      failStep:1, failNote:&quot;can't chain 3 models&quot;}\n  };\n  var STEPS = [\n    {n:&quot;Select model&quot;, note:&quot;matches goal to a skill&quot;},\n    {n:&quot;Prepare inputs&quot;, note:&quot;format + parameters&quot;},\n    {n:&quot;Run NIM&quot;, note:&quot;hosted or local endpoint&quot;},\n    {n:&quot;Inspect output&quot;, note:&quot;read returned artifact&quot;},\n    {n:&quot;Explain result&quot;, note:&quot;with scientific caveats&quot;}\n  ];\n\n  var current = &quot;fold&quot;, skillsOn = true, running = false, timers = [];\n  var $ = function(id){return document.getElementById(id)};\n\n  // build task cards\n  var tasksEl = $(&quot;bnTasks&quot;);\n  Object.keys(TASKS).forEach(function(k){\n    var t = TASKS[k];\n    var b = document.createElement(&quot;button&quot;);\n    b.className = &quot;bn-task&quot; + (k===current?&quot; is-on&quot;:&quot;&quot;);\n    b.setAttribute(&quot;data-k&quot;, k);\n    b.innerHTML = '&lt;span class=&quot;bn-task-ico&quot;&gt;'+t.icon+'&lt;/span&gt;'+\n      '&lt;span class=&quot;bn-task-name&quot;&gt;'+t.name+'&lt;/span&gt;'+\n      '&lt;span class=&quot;bn-task-skill&quot;&gt;'+t.skill+'&lt;/span&gt;';\n    b.addEventListener(&quot;click&quot;, function(){\n      if(running) return;\n      current = k;\n      [].forEach.call(tasksEl.children, function(c){c.classList.remove(&quot;is-on&quot;)});\n      b.classList.add(&quot;is-on&quot;);\n      resetLoop();\n    });\n    tasksEl.appendChild(b);\n  });\n\n  // build steps\n  var stepsEl = $(&quot;bnSteps&quot;);\n  function renderSteps(){\n    stepsEl.innerHTML = &quot;&quot;;\n    STEPS.forEach(function(s,i){\n      var li = document.createElement(&quot;li&quot;);\n      li.className = &quot;bn-step&quot;;\n      li.innerHTML = '&lt;span class=&quot;bn-dot&quot;&gt;'+(i+1)+'&lt;/span&gt;'+\n        '&lt;div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;bn-step-name&quot;&gt;'+s.n+'&lt;/div&gt;'+\n        '&lt;div class=&quot;bn-step-note&quot;&gt;'+s.note+'&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;';\n      stepsEl.appendChild(li);\n    });\n  }\n  renderSteps();\n\n  // skills toggle\n  var tog = $(&quot;bnSkillToggle&quot;);\n  function setToggle(){\n    tog.classList.toggle(&quot;is-on&quot;, skillsOn);\n    tog.setAttribute(&quot;aria-checked&quot;, skillsOn);\n    $(&quot;bnToggleSub&quot;).textContent = skillsOn ? &quot;On — agent reads the skill&quot; : &quot;Off — agent guesses&quot;;\n  }\n  tog.addEventListener(&quot;click&quot;, function(){ if(running) return; skillsOn=!skillsOn; setToggle(); resetLoop(); });\n  tog.addEventListener(&quot;keydown&quot;, function(e){ if(e.key===&quot; &quot;||e.key===&quot;Enter&quot;){e.preventDefault();tog.click();} });\n\n  function clearTimers(){ timers.forEach(clearTimeout); timers=[]; }\n\n  function resetLoop(){\n    clearTimers(); running=false;\n    var t = TASKS[current];\n    $(&quot;bnCap&quot;).textContent = t.cap;\n    $(&quot;bnModel&quot;).textContent = t.model;\n    $(&quot;bnInput&quot;).textContent = t.input;\n    $(&quot;bnArtType&quot;).textContent = skillsOn ? t.artifact : &quot;unknown&quot;;\n    renderSteps();\n    var st = $(&quot;bnStatus&quot;);\n    st.className = &quot;bn-status idle&quot;;\n    st.textContent = &quot;Ready — press Run agent loop.&quot;;\n    setBars(skillsOn ? 100 : 57.1, skillsOn ? 100 : 50);\n    $(&quot;bnComplVal&quot;).textContent = skillsOn ? &quot;100%&quot; : &quot;57.1%&quot;;\n    $(&quot;bnEffVal&quot;).textContent = skillsOn ? &quot;2.0×&quot; : &quot;1.0×&quot;;\n  }\n\n  function setBars(compl, eff){\n    $(&quot;bnComplBar&quot;).style.width = compl + &quot;%&quot;;\n    $(&quot;bnEffBar&quot;).style.width = eff + &quot;%&quot;;\n  }\n\n  $(&quot;bnRun&quot;).addEventListener(&quot;click&quot;, function(){\n    if(running) return;\n    running = true; clearTimers();\n    var t = TASKS[current];\n    var btn = $(&quot;bnRun&quot;); btn.disabled = true; btn.textContent = &quot;Running…&quot;;\n    renderSteps();\n    var lis = stepsEl.children;\n    setBars(0,0);\n    var st = $(&quot;bnStatus&quot;); st.className=&quot;bn-status idle&quot;; st.textContent=&quot;Working…&quot;;\n\n    var stopAt = skillsOn ? STEPS.length : t.failStep + 1; // no-skill run fails early\n    var i = 0;\n    function tick(){\n      // close previous\n      if(i&gt;0){\n        var prev = lis[i-1];\n        prev.classList.remove(&quot;is-live&quot;);\n        prev.classList.add(&quot;is-done&quot;);\n      }\n      if(i &gt;= stopAt){ finish(); return; }\n      var li = lis[i];\n      li.classList.add(&quot;is-live&quot;);\n      // last reached step in no-skill mode becomes a failure\n      var isFailHere = (!skillsOn &amp;&amp; i === t.failStep);\n      if(isFailHere){\n        timers.push(setTimeout(function(){\n          li.classList.remove(&quot;is-live&quot;); li.classList.add(&quot;is-fail&quot;);\n          li.querySelector(&quot;.bn-dot&quot;).textContent=&quot;!&quot;;\n          li.querySelector(&quot;.bn-step-note&quot;).textContent = t.failNote;\n          finish();\n        }, 650));\n        return;\n      }\n      // annotate prepare step with a real note\n      if(i===1 &amp;&amp; skillsOn){ li.querySelector(&quot;.bn-step-note&quot;).textContent = t.prepNote; }\n      i++;\n      timers.push(setTimeout(tick, 620));\n    }\n\n    function finish(){\n      var st = $(&quot;bnStatus&quot;);\n      if(skillsOn){\n        st.className=&quot;bn-status ok&quot;;\n        st.textContent = &quot;\\u2713 Completed · returned &quot; + t.artifact;\n        animateBars(100,100,&quot;100%&quot;,&quot;2.0×&quot;);\n      } else {\n        st.className=&quot;bn-status warn&quot;;\n        st.textContent = &quot;\\u26A0 Stalled · &quot; + t.failNote;\n        animateBars(57.1,50,&quot;57.1%&quot;,&quot;1.0×&quot;);\n      }\n      running=false; btn.disabled=false; btn.textContent=&quot;Run agent loop&quot;;\n      postSize();\n    }\n    timers.push(setTimeout(tick, 120));\n  });\n\n  function animateBars(compl, eff, cTxt, eTxt){\n    setBars(0,0);\n    timers.push(setTimeout(function(){\n      setBars(compl, eff);\n      $(&quot;bnComplVal&quot;).textContent=cTxt; $(&quot;bnEffVal&quot;).textContent=eTxt;\n    }, 80));\n  }\n\n  // init\n  setToggle();\n  resetLoop();\n\n  // auto-resize for WordPress iframe embed (component height + buffer)\n  function postSize(){\n    var h = document.getElementById(&quot;bnRoot&quot;).offsetHeight + 40;\n    if(window.parent){ window.parent.postMessage({bionemoHeight:h}, &quot;*&quot;); }\n  }\n  window.addEventListener(&quot;load&quot;, postSize);\n  window.addEventListener(&quot;resize&quot;, postSize);\n  setTimeout(postSize, 300);\n})();\n&lt;/script&gt;\n&lt;/body&gt;\n&lt;/html&gt;\n\"></iframe>\n  <p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\"></p>\n  <p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">The BioNeMo Agent Toolkit is an open-source repository of ‘skills’ for AI agents. Each skill turns an NVIDIA biomolecular model into a tool an agent can call. The toolkit packages protein folding, molecular docking, generative chemistry, genomics analysis, protein design, and biomarker discovery.</p>\n  <p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">NVIDIA frames the platform in two parts. The first is an accelerated tool layer. NVIDIA NIM (NVIDIA Inference Microservices) and BioNeMo open models deliver core capabilities as callable services. These are accelerated by libraries such as cuEquivariance for structure models and Parabricks for genomics. The second part is agent-ready interfaces. BioNeMo Skills package each capability so an agent can use it.</p>\n  <p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">A skill documents the model’s purpose, required inputs, optional parameters, expected artifacts, and failure modes. Model Context Protocol (MCP) server wrappers expose open models not yet packaged as NIM. Together, this lets an agent discover, select, invoke, and interpret biomolecular models on its own.</p>\n  <p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">The repository groups skills into <code>nim-skills</code>, <code>open-models-skills</code>, and <code>library-skills</code>. A <code>workflows</code> folder holds multi-step meta-skills. One example is <code>generative_protein_binder_design</code>, which chains RFdiffusion → ProteinMPNN → OpenFold3.</p>\n  <h2 id=\"h-how-a-bionemo-skill-works\" class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>How a BioNeMo Skill Works</strong></h2>\n  <p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">Every skill is a directory with a <code>SKILL.md</code> file. It holds YAML frontmatter plus instructions, optional references, and optional scripts. An agent reads it like documentation, then acts on it.</p>\n  <p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">The prompt pattern stays the same across models. The NVIDIA’s post uses OpenFold3. The same shape applies to other NIMs for biology. These include Boltz-2, DiffDock, GenMol, ProteinMPNN, MSA Search, RFdiffusion, and Evo 2. You name the skill, the input, and the endpoint.</p>\n  <div class=\"dm-code-snippet dark dm-normal-version default no-background-mobile\" snippet-height=\"\" style=\"background-color:#abb8c3\">\n   <div class=\"control-language\">\n    <div class=\"dm-buttons\">\n     <div class=\"dm-buttons-left\"></div>\n     <div class=\"dm-buttons-right\">\n      <a id=\"dm-copy-raw-code\"><span class=\"dm-copy-text\">Copy Code</span></a>\n     </div>\n    </div>\n    <pre class=\" no-line-numbers\"><code id=\"dm-code-raw\" class=\" no-wrap language-php\"># Hosted NIM endpoint\nUse the OpenFold3 BioNeMo Skill to fold MKTVRQERLKSIVR\nwith the NVIDIA API endpoint at https://build.nvidia.com/openfold3\n\n# Local NIM deployment\nUse the OpenFold3 BioNeMo Skill to fold MKTVRQERLKSIVR\nwith the local NIM endpoint at http://localhost:8000</code></pre>\n   </div>\n  </div>\n  <p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">Installation pulls skills through the open-source <code>skills</code> CLI:</p>\n  <div class=\"dm-code-snippet dark dm-normal-version default no-background-mobile\" snippet-height=\"\" style=\"background-color:#abb8c3\">\n   <div class=\"control-language\">\n    <div class=\"dm-buttons\">\n     <div class=\"dm-buttons-left\"></div>\n     <div class=\"dm-buttons-right\">\n      <a id=\"dm-copy-raw-code\"><span class=\"dm-copy-text\">Copy Code</span></a>\n     </div>\n    </div>\n    <pre class=\" no-line-numbers\"><code id=\"dm-code-raw\" class=\" no-wrap language-php\"># Browse and pick a skill interactively\nnpx skills add NVIDIA-BioNeMo/bionemo-agent-toolkit\n\n# Or install one skill for a specific agent\nnpx skills add NVIDIA-BioNeMo/bionemo-agent-toolkit --skill boltz2-nim --agent claude-code</code></pre>\n   </div>\n  </div>\n  <p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">Deployment is a choice, not a default. Use hosted NIM endpoints for fast access without managing infrastructure. Move selected models local when you need lower warm latency, data locality, or repeated iteration.</p>\n  <h2 id=\"h-benchmark\" class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>Benchmark</strong></h2>\n  <p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">NVIDIA measured whether skills actually improve an agent’s loop. All reported metrics came from Codex CLI running GPT-5.5 fast. The team compared the same agent with and without each skill.</p>\n  <p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">Task completion was the first metric. Without skills, the agent completed 57.1% of required tasks on average. With access to NIM skills, completion reached 100%.</p>\n  <p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">Efficiency was the second metric. NVIDIA counted passing assertions, the individual steps that compose a task. With skills, an agent produced 2x more passing assertions per 1,000 tokens. That gain held across all ten NIM skills tested.</p>\n  <h2 id=\"h-use-cases-with-examples\" class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>Use Cases With Examples</strong></h2>\n  <ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n   <li><strong>Protein structure prediction</strong>: An agent folds a peptide sequence with Boltz-2 or OpenFold3. It returns a CIF file for downstream inspection.</li>\n   <li><strong>Multiple sequence alignment</strong>: An agent generates an MSA with MMseqs2 through the MSA Search skill. The artifact is an A3M file.</li>\n   <li><strong>Generative chemistry</strong>: An agent generates candidate molecules with GenMol. Outputs arrive as SDF or SMILES for filtering.</li>\n   <li><strong>Protein binder design</strong>: The <code>generative_protein_binder_design</code> workflow chains three models. RFdiffusion builds a backbone, ProteinMPNN designs the sequence, and OpenFold3 validates the fold.</li>\n   <li><strong>Each loop follows the same shape: </strong>The agent selects a model, prepares inputs, runs it, inspects outputs, and explains results with caveats.</li>\n  </ul>\n  <h2 id=\"h-how-it-compares-agent-with-vs-without-skills\" class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>How It Compares: Agent With vs Without Skills</strong></h2>\n  <figure class=\"wp-block-table is-style-stripes\">\n   <table class=\"has-fixed-layout\">\n    <thead>\n     <tr>\n      <th>Dimension</th>\n      <th>General agent (no skills)</th>\n      <th>Agent + BioNeMo Skills</th>\n     </tr>\n    </thead>\n    <tbody>\n     <tr>\n      <td>Task completion</td>\n      <td>57.1% average</td>\n      <td>100% average</td>\n     </tr>\n     <tr>\n      <td>Token efficiency</td>\n      <td>Baseline</td>\n      <td>2x passing assertions per 1k tokens</td>\n     </tr>\n     <tr>\n      <td>Model selection</td>\n      <td>Guesses tool, format, and inputs</td>\n      <td>Reads purpose, inputs, and artifacts</td>\n     </tr>\n     <tr>\n      <td>Deployment</td>\n      <td>Manual setup from source</td>\n      <td>Hosted or local NIM, documented</td>\n     </tr>\n     <tr>\n      <td>Failure handling</td>\n      <td>Unknown failure modes</td>\n      <td>Documented failure modes per skill</td>\n     </tr>\n     <tr>\n      <td>Workflows</td>\n      <td>Isolated single calls</td>\n      <td>Multi-step meta-skills (binder design)</td>\n     </tr>\n    </tbody>\n   </table>\n  </figure>\n  <h2 id=\"h-getting-started\" class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>Getting Started</strong></h2>\n  <p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">The prerequisites are minimal. You need an agent runtime such as Claude or Codex. You need an NVIDIA API key for hosted BioNeMo NIM endpoints. A GPU node is optional, for local NIM deployment.</p>\n  <p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">Point the agent at the repository first. Let it enumerate the available capabilities before it acts. Then hand it a single skill to operate one model.</p>\n  <p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">NVIDIA flags two cautions. The <code>build.nvidia.com</code> endpoints are for small-scale development and testing only. They are not production-grade inference. NVIDIA also stresses validation: check low-confidence structures and filter generated molecules before trusting them.</p>\n  <p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\"></p>\n  <hr class=\"wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity\">\n  <p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\"></p>\n  <p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">Check out the&nbsp;<strong><a href=\"https://github.com/NVIDIA-BioNeMo/bionemo-agent-toolkit\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">Repo</a>&nbsp;</strong>and<strong>&nbsp;<a href=\"https://developer.nvidia.com/blog/build-an-ai-scientist-for-life-science-discovery-with-nvidia-bionemo-agent-toolkit/?ncid=so-twit-130411\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">Technical details</a></strong>.<strong>&nbsp;</strong>Also,&nbsp;feel free to follow us on&nbsp;<strong><a href=\"https://x.com/intent/follow?screen_name=marktechpost\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\"><mark>Twitter</mark></a></strong>&nbsp;and don’t forget to join our&nbsp;<strong><a href=\"https://www.reddit.com/r/machinelearningnews/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">150k+ML SubReddit</a></strong>&nbsp;and Subscribe to&nbsp;<strong><a href=\"https://www.aidevsignals.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">our Newsletter</a></strong>. Wait! are you on telegram?&nbsp;<strong><a href=\"https://t.me/machinelearningresearchnews\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">now you can join us on telegram as well.</a></strong></p>\n  <p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">Need to partner with us for promoting your GitHub Repo OR Hugging Face Page OR Product Release OR Webinar etc.?&nbsp;<strong><a href=\"https://forms.gle/wbash1wF6efRj8G58\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\"><mark>Connect with us</mark></a></strong></p>\n  <!-- MOLONGUI AUTHORSHIP PLUGIN 5.2.9 -->\n  <!-- https://www.molongui.com/wordpress-plugin-post-authors -->\n  <!-- CONTENT END 2 -->\n  <div class=\"td-a-rec td-a-rec-id-content_bottom  tdi_77 td_block_template_1\">\n   <div id=\"bsad-700x300\">\n    <div class=\"bs-stage\">\n     <div class=\"bs-scale\">\n      <a class=\"bs-ad\" href=\"https://pxllnk.co/cuv4rk8\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\" aria-label=\"BigSet on GitHub — describe your ideal dataset in plain English, and BigSet builds it\"> \n       <div class=\"wrap\">\n        <div class=\"left\">\n         <div class=\"kicker\">\n          <span class=\"brand\"><span class=\"dot\"></span>tinyfish.ai</span><span class=\"pill\">Open Source</span>\n         </div>\n         <div class=\"name\">\n          Big<b>Set</b>\n         </div>\n         <div class=\"tag\">Describe your ideal dataset in plain English, and BigSet builds it.</div>\n        </div>\n        <div class=\"right\">\n         <div class=\"cta\">\n          <span>Explore on GitHub</span><span class=\"arrow\">→</span>\n         </div>\n        </div>\n       </div> \n      </a>\n     </div>\n    </div>\n   </div>\n  </div>\n </body>\n</html>",
  "aiSummary": "NVIDIA 的 BioNeMo 智能体工具包将生物分子模型封装为 AI 智能体的可调用技能，凭借具备文档说明且以工具为核心的能力，将药物发现任务完成率从 57.1% 提升至 100%。",
